This paper deals with the degrees of freedom of interference channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves cooperation among transmitters, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper discusses message assignments and their impact on the per user DoF number, which could be considered a problem in optimization (cs.OH) or machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of local cooperation constraints, which could be related to signal processing (cs.SP) or communication engineering (cs.CE).
